# <type>[optional scope]: <description>
#
# [optional body]
#
# [optional footer(s)]

# Types:
# feat:     A new feature
# fix:      A bug fix
# docs:     Documentation only changes
# style:    Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code
# refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# perf:     A code change that improves performance
# test:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
# chore:    Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools

# Examples:
# feat: add backup-stats command
# fix: resolve config file parsing issue
# docs: update installation instructions
# feat!: remove deprecated API (BREAKING CHANGE)
# fix(completion): handle missing config gracefully

# Breaking Changes:
# Add BREAKING CHANGE: in the footer or use ! after type/scope
# This will trigger a MAJOR version bump

# Scope examples: completion, backup, config, install, test